                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="" height="147">
                   <tr> 
                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>What parsing and mathematical models completely miss (and this is revealed in Absor's bizarre reference to m&#111;nks as "uber tanks") are things like the extreme difficulty in grabbing agro in the first place RELIABLY over a hard healing cleric and a hard slowing chanter. Thinking about mob "jitter" al&#111;ne (i.e. propensity of a sow'd mob to move to a new target faster than most c&#111;nnecti&#111;ns can readily keep up with) and the fact that our &#111;nly taunt is close up melee damage + disarm (&lt;&lt; range than taunt skill) brings home the serious limitati&#111;ns of a m&#111;nk tanking that SoE's analysis totally ignored.</P>
<P>This al&#111;ne makes a beastlord a far better tank (for example) than a m&#111;nk, regardless of models. Even if the BL has to be healed more, it's still worth it since the agro will be more reliable. Yes, there's root, but that means (1) no DD proccing weap&#111;ns can be used by any&#111;ne, and (2) situati&#111;nal use &#111;nly; not great vs very MR mobs.</P>
<P>Having said that, (and not wishing to simply complain) I agree with what people above are saying. Given that we are going to be stuck with a nerf based &#111;n math rather than the game and how it's played, developers should be looking at the following:</P>
<P>(1) m&#111;nk weap&#111;ns are indeed hard to obtain. There is no weap&#111;n that procs slow for instance; every other class gets &#111;ne; we d&#111;n't. Now that our ability to solo has been hit hard, could SoE not introduce weap&#111;ns that proc slow (with unlimited charges of course; I'm not referring to that st&#111;ne that drops in hate).</P>
<P>Another tool m&#111;nks could use is the ability to pull rapidly from very l&#111;ng range: an instacast moderately low agro range 300+ (so we can at least compete with people with bows) pulling item would be a nice start, and please, no charges. (In an ideal world, it wouldn't break sneak either!)</P>
<P>(2) Many m&#111;nk offensive AA's are DESIGNED for us to be tanking. Double Riposte, Return Kick, Flash of Steel. Given that we are not to be tanks, surely the fact that two thirds of our Luclin offensive class AA's require us to be tanking could be looked at? To ignore this is to treat the m&#111;nk class with a very c&#111;nsiderable degree of detachment from reality!</P>
<P>(3) The ability to be the best close range melee damage from all angles is nearly useless in PoP for the following reas&#111;ns: <BR>a) ripostes. Thanks to lag, I got stuck &#111;n the wr&#111;ng side of Aerin`Dar for two ripostes. Thanks to the m&#111;nk nerf, I took nearly 2900 damage from those two. <BR>b) AE's. The advantage of a ranger to stand at range and do damage is incalculable. Team Ranger provides far far more utility than Team M&#111;nk to a guild raid, particularly in PoP.<BR>c) The idea that we actually ARE the best at melee damage from all angles can certainly be debated: there are a number of parses showing a mediocrely equipped BL (with pet) matching a well-equipped m&#111;nk in damage, and a well-equipped BL exceeding.<BR>d) Ditto (c) for mages. Ditto (c) for a well-equipped bard going for damage &#111;nly. (Note that this would be stupid as the bard's group buffs will do more damage than a bard going &#111;n all out damage, but this too says something about a m&#111;nk's lack of group utility).</P>
<P>(4) Pulling. The fact that so many PoP z&#111;nes are outdoor, and so few mobs summ&#111;n, and mobs tend to be easily rootable make it highly questi&#111;nable that we remain the best pullers. Add the fact that SK's now have harmshield (just before PoP), 2x the FD cycle time as m&#111;nks, snare, ability to pull from range, and it really is questi&#111;nable. How to fix that without nerfing other classes? I've no idea.</P>
