                 <td valign="top"> 
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="" height="147">
                   <tr> 
                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>The m&#111;nk nerf went in the right directi&#111;n, but it unfortunately went a mile too far.</P>
<P>M&#111;nks were not unbalanced or too powerful at lower levels or prior to having a full set of Vex Thal gear. So what they really needed to do, was&nbsp;softcap m&#111;nk AC. If they didn't want m&#111;nks to tank better than&nbsp;1300 AC maximum, then they should have capped it there, crippling the 1600 ac uber m&#111;nks but leaving average level&nbsp;60's and every&#111;ne below them al&#111;ne.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>In left it's current state, it's already been correctly noted that&nbsp;VI wants&nbsp;pure melees to tank&nbsp;in relati&#111;n to their damage dealing capabilities. &nbsp;Since rogues outdamage us from levels 10-65 by a good 50&#037; or greater up until the absolute best gear in the game becomes available, the soluti&#111;n is simple. Make m&#111;nks deal more damage. Make higher end m&#111;nk weap&#111;ns readily available. Provide an innate ATK b&#111;nus to m&#111;nks. Improve the effects of special attacks, possibly adding the 2h damage b&#111;nus to them, etc. (I particularly like using special attacks to increase our damage, as it helps all m&#111;nks regardless of equipment levels equally, and counters the rogue means of doing damage--the special effect Backstab.) In the current state of tanking affairs, m&#111;nks need to outdamage rogues at ALL times, even when both are fighting from behind a mob. It's either that, or completely remove the nerf altogether, which is not the purpose of this thread.</P><!-- Signature --><br><br><span style="font-size:9px;">-----------------</span><br><img border="0" src= "http://purpletel.com/d.jpg"><br>
<a target="_blank" href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=192025">Sensei Deirdre Sadiqa</a><br>
