                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>Taken from the original book that came with my eq :</P>
<P>M&#111;nks: The m&#111;nk is dedicated to h&#111;ning her body into a pure weap&#111;n, shunning most weap&#111;ns and &#102;orms of armor. She's very religous as well, and the gods are known to bless M&#111;nks by magically ehancing their attacks.</P>
<P>When I decided to make my character this original de&#115;cripti&#111;n is what did it for me. I loved playing my m&#111;nk through the levels, watching him improve and having a great time. I can still remember crawling thorugh dalnir for that first piece of great armor to replace that cured silk. I remeber the joy of getting that first wu stick and even greater the feeling of completing the epic and havin the bubbles. Velious was a glimpse at our class rising to power, and luclin with alt points and equipment made us very str&#111;ng. </P>
<P>It seems to me like a good majority of the people would like to see an ac soft cap, cause of the problems at lower levels. The &#111;nly problem with that is why keep pushing forward and equipping yourselves, getting alternate points to catch up to where we were 6-8 m&#111;nths ago. However soe decides to fix us it has to be a soluti&#111;n that the people who already worked for this equipment, not bought, raided or grouped for get improvements inline with the rest of the classes at each level and gear range. </P>
<P>A few ideas to throw &#111;n to the table that could help us i do believe. First off raise the damage &#111;n minimum and maximum flying kicks to be more inline with weap&#111;n damage. If you can use a h2h weap&#111;n and hit for over 120, 300 would seem to be more inline with power of a fist over the power of a kick. Avoiding all ripostes to allow us to fight from every angle would be another nice additi&#111;n. Looking at our avoidance verse warrior and rogue and raise it some. Last but not least make it so fd does not fail anymore. After playing for 65 levels, hundreds of alternate points it would be nice to too fail fd anymore. </P>
<P>I still enjoy playing this game and the encounters in PoP so far have been great fun and challenges. I hope that they realise that not &#111;nly m&#111;nks, but pure melee in general were shafted so far in this expansi&#111;n.</P>
<P>Algorres</P><!-- Message body ''"" --></td>
