                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>C&#111;nsidering our current role in groups and in raids is to do two things...&#079;ne, pull mobs and two, deal damage.&nbsp; Given that I'd like to see the SOE folks do two things to slightly adjust our class.</P>
<P>First, I'd like to see our damage table upped just a tad, to where we are &#111;n par with rogues throughout all levels...provided we aren't acting as the tank.&nbsp; By this I mean that if we are going toe-to-toe with a mob our damage should be less than if we are hitting from the side or behind.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Now it currently is that way to some degree but I'd like to see our FK skill become highly lethal at the later levels, similar to the backstab skill of the rogue.&nbsp; Meaning that if we are FKing from the side or behind the mob, the damage increases significantly.&nbsp; I believe this is a very pure part of our role.&nbsp; It isn't weap&#111;n or armor based, it is based &#111;n the purest sense of the m&#111;nk class...using our bodies to deal damage...lots of damage.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>The sec&#111;nd thing I'd like to see changed slightly is our ability to avoid damage from behind.&nbsp; Thus when we are pulling we take less damage and can survive the high end pulls of places like Ntov.&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
