                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>I would sum to three major revisi&#111;ns needed:</P>
<P>1) Increase avg DPS, but not via Flying Kick.&nbsp; If we focus &#111;n getting a better Flying Kick, doesn't it just become another Backstab?&nbsp; I'd rather see our standard DPS raised. and I think the easiest way to do this is give us the chance for *crits* like other melees, and not just to kicking via AA's.&nbsp; Then they d&#111;n't&nbsp;even need to&nbsp;change the dmg&nbsp;tables.</P>
<P>2) Some sort of innate or triggered dmg avoidance from the rear.&nbsp; Even making us unstunnable from the rear like ogres are from the fr&#111;nt would be a huge benefit.&nbsp; Perhaps a voiddance type disc that still allows the possibility of being hit, but has a much shorter timer.&nbsp; &#079;ne proposal for the name could be Sense Attacks.</P>
<P>3) Allow for FD while autoattack is &#111;n (again?).&nbsp; I agree with the fact that casters can break FD, and I d&#111;n't ask that the success rate be improved for FD overall, but too often a FD fails even after attack is off due to lag.&nbsp; D&#111;n't penalize us for laggy servers.&nbsp; It makes no sense for attack to autofail a FD.</P>
<P>If we were given these three changes, I believe we would benefit greatly, and it would allow us to solidify some sort of role.&nbsp; If we can't be the best dmg mitigator, can't be the best dmg dealer, and can't cast, then we have to be allowed to excel at pulling.&nbsp; There is no other role left that we can fill.&nbsp; Give the rogues above-and-bey&#111;nd dmg, let us slide into the sec&#111;nd spot, and give us something which elevates us above SK pullers, because we have nothing to distinguish us from them now, in fact, as a plate class, they are the best of both worlds.</P><!-- Message body ''"" --></td>
