                   <tr> 
                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>That wouldn't fix the balance issue we have now.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Ignore pulling, it's not a factor in balance.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Combat balance is comprised of three main things:</P>
<P>Offensive Ability</P>
<P>Defensive Ability</P>
<P>Support Ability (buffs, heals, existing crowd/add c&#111;ntrol, etc.)</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>If you rate pure melees &#111;n their own, n&#111;ne of us have any substantial support ability, so it makes it easy. You &#111;nly need to rate offense and defense. If you rated &#111;n a scale of 1-10, with 5 being average, you could rate warriors as&nbsp;6 &#111;n offense, 10 &#111;n defense. Rogues are 10 &#111;n offense,&nbsp;6 &#111;n defense. M&#111;nks are currently 7 &#111;n offense, and maybe 4 &#111;n defense &#111;n a good day. Hybrids get their support ability mixed into the fray, so paladins might have 9 defense and &#111;nly 4 offense, but they have 3-4 points of support ability (compared to a cleric's 10 for instance.) Add em all up for standing, and m&#111;nks have a problem. We have the worst defense, and &#111;nly midrange offense.&nbsp; The other hybrids would have various balance states as well, probably all equalling a warrior or rogue overall.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Since a m&#111;nk has no support abilities, the &#111;nly way to address the balance issue is to either (A) Improve offensive abilities, or (B) remove the nerf entirely and allow defensive abilities. In neither case should these soluti&#111;ns be reliant &#111;n equipment, but should be natural improvements that affect the entire m&#111;nk class equally at the same level of experience.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P><!-- Signature --><br><br><span style="font-size:9px;">-----------------</span><br><img border="0" src= "http://purpletel.com/d.jpg"><br>
<a target="_blank" href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=192025">Sensei Deirdre Sadiqa</a><br>
<i> Crouching Tigress Training Drag&#111;ns</i><!-- Signature --><!-- Message body ''"" --></td>
