                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>What was S&#111;ny's goal with the M&#111;nk changes exactly?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Well, they resp&#111;nded to the ability of M&#111;nks to Tank HighEnd Mobs because of their Avoidance capabilities at the upper tiers... trickling down from there...</P>
<P>Hrmm... If they are c&#111;ncerned with primarily the higher end top 5&#037; of M&#111;nks... the change shouldn't be directly affecting Core M&#111;nk Defensive&nbsp;numbers so much as the HIGH All/All armor HP &amp; AC capabilities from where I see it... The highest leevl m&#111;nks found the changes to have little to no affect over them because their gear compensated for that...</P>
<P>Comparatively, Old World / Kunark and pre-top tier of Velious gear for m&#111;nks is lacking a lot in AC/HP area... it isn't until you see the gear that comes from killing the 3 Velious Kings (Yeli, Tormax, and Dain) that does gear begin to rapidly increase a M&#111;nk's standard tankability...&nbsp; Add in Luclin gear which is leaps and bounds above other Armor for M&#111;nks (Acrylia, Goranga Idols,&nbsp;some of the easily dropped items) and you see another small boost... Then with upper Luclin/Vex Thal gear M&#111;nk Tanking goes even higher...</P>
<P>The problem seems to lie with the gear, low wt. ALL / ALL gear is often looked at as a MNK item and Verant has stated they didn't intend this persay in "The Visi&#111;n"</P>
<P>The potential cure?&nbsp; Retroactive item nerfs are a VERY BAD thing... but what about modifying the AC soft caps and/or reducing the amount of AC awarded post-softcap?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>I d&#111;n't know whether the AC softcap can be set for different levels, or whether it can be &#111;nly used for teh upper cap al&#111;ne...&nbsp; suppose it's &#111;nly at the upper end, I haven't seen info that it can or is d&#111;ne the other way...</P>
<P>If you want to lower top-geared m&#111;nks from tanking... then cut the softcap down some... I d&#111;n't know what a 100 or 200 point AC shift in the Softcap would do to change m&#111;nk tanking... and I d&#111;n't know exactly where the softcap is at (some&#111;ne please help who has that info)&nbsp; but that would readily lower High end m&#111;nk tanking mobs... also, softcap means AC bey&#111;nd that point gives reduced b&#111;nus... if it's at say 4 points postsoftcapAC = 1&nbsp;additi&#111;nal AC... MAYBE&nbsp;change postsoftcap rate to&nbsp;be 5 or 6 points = 1 point AC boost...</P>
<P>Depends &#111;n where the Softcap currently is, and how well the upper&nbsp;5&#037; of m&#111;nks&nbsp;rank above it...&nbsp;</P>
<P>Meanwhile, restore about 80-90&#037; of the change to the Core M&#111;nk defensive abilities...&nbsp; The changes hit any lower level m&#111;nks who were unable to compete with the softcap FAR too hard... This still modifies where they were for lowering some ability to tank, but at these levels it was much harder to sustain Tanking/maintain aggro...</P>
<P><BR>Possibly, in c&#111;njuncti&#111;n with the AC changes... like stated above... a M&#111;nk upgrade in weap&#111;n choice and damage output is needed... they aren't comparing to other melees the way S&#111;ny thinks they are...&nbsp; If S&#111;ny wants them to be the Best All-Around meleers and worst melee tank... then they need to have DPS to surpass Rogues from the back... OR come frighteningly close to Rogue damage ( i know scary thought, d&#111;n't know if M&#111;nks SHOULD be up there, but depends &#111;n where S&#111;ny wants us to be)</P>
