                 <td valign="top"> 
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="" height="147">
                   <tr> 
                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>There isn't an AC softcap, and you can't just change the softcap for m&#111;nks.</P>
<P>AC is made up of 2 factors: avoidance and mitigati&#111;n. M&#111;nks happen to have more &#111;n the avoidance part while Warriors have more mitigati&#111;n with the same AC value. Avoidance cannot possibly be changed significantly, increasing Agi helps a tad, but the huge factors are class, level, defensive skill.</P>
<P>Avoidance isn't where the so called softcap hits in, it's the mitigati&#111;n. Basically there's a point of mitigati&#111;n AC where adding more doesn't help, which is based &#111;n the mob you're facing and is checked against the ATK of the mob. Of course mobs in the same z&#111;ne tend to have a similar ATK. People have talked about AC cap based &#111;n expansi&#111;ns, but it just happens that the highest ATK mob in say Luclin have similar ATK (i.e. comm&#111;n mobs in Ssra, Akheva, Acrylia). This is why they thought it's an expansi&#111;n based AC cap.</P>
<P>Let's assume that the comm&#111;n high level mobs (n&#111;n-bosses) in Luclin all have around 1500 ATK, this means that you will stop taking less damage at 1500 AC (actually it's much more complicated). So for EACH mob with the same ATK adding AC doesn't help.</P>
<P>What SoE did was nerf our mitigati&#111;n table so m&#111;nks now need more mitigati&#111;n AC to take minimum damage (or even start not taking maximum damage). What the f**kers didn't realize is that VT m&#111;nks STILL MITIGATE THE MAJORITY OF THE MOBS DAMAGE, because they have much higher mitigati&#111;n AC then the rest of the m&#111;nks. What they SHOULD have made is that mitigati&#111;n AC&nbsp;over a certain value &#111;nly adds half as much or something (which in fact would be a softcap), or just retr&#111;nerf certain m&#111;nk armor like the AoW leggings and most VT stuff, but of course that would've pissed off uber guilds which SoE doesn't want, they much rather nerf 90&#037; of the m&#111;nks.</P><!-- Signature --><br><br><span style="font-size:9px;">-----------------</span><br><a target="_blank" href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27300">Oracle J&#111;naman McWolfspirit</a><br>
<a target="_blank" href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27307">Grandmaster Kshaaz</a><br>
Britannic Lore<!-- Signature --><!-- Message body ''"" --></td>
                   </tr>
                  </table>
                 </td>
