                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>I play a m&#111;nk and a ranger and altough I visited MB frequnetly I didn't &#111;nce post there due to the hostility directed at any&#111;ne with a differing veiwpoint.</P>
<P>I do think there's a need to restore some of the loss back to the m&#111;nk class but I would imagine it's a nightmare for the developers to implement a fix that hits &#111;nly their intended populati&#111;n and leaves the vast majority of m&#111;nks unaffected.</P>
<P>We need to be rati&#111;nal as a class.I see many posts &#111;n MB comparing pure melee (particularily m&#111;nks) to Hybrids (mostly Rangers) and as always there's an immense amount of misin&#102;ormati&#111;n included.</P>
<P>Let's take bow damage.To achieve anything like decent bow DPS the Ranger must first get level 59 (most likely 60) and 45 aa points,there is no short cut or quicker way and even then the claims of 1800-2000 crits are somewhat wide of the mark.While it is possible to score crits to those values they are extremely rare and require a high end bow(from the same kind of bosses those hard to get m&#111;nk weap&#111;ns drop from),uber shammy buffs and a very high base of dexterity.Then factor in that if the mob is touching a wall,a player runs in the way,there is a blade of grass model between the ranger and the mob archery does zero damage.Around 40&#037; of my arrows simply disappear during archery and it's also worth bearing in mind that Trueshot is a 2 minute discipline with a 72 minute refresh and requires line of sight and enough room to actually shoot the mob.</P>
<P>Spells can be useful but with the large amount of right clickables and procs they're really no reas&#111;n for envy.</P>
<P>Hybrids also get much less in the way of disciplines,at level 61 my ranger has &#111;nly 4,including resistant and fearless.</P>
<P>M&#111;nks need some kind of fix but DPS increases is not that fix.The nerf hurt our ability to stand toe to toe with a mob as its main focus of attack it did not reduce an already impressive DPS and the ability of m&#111;nks with less than stellar equipment to tank,no damage mobs is what needs to be adressed.</P>
<P>Apart from this m&#111;nks are not in bad shape.We get effects &#111;n our quest armour &#111;n more pieces than other melee classes,good all round abilities,high skill caps that allow us to outdamage hybrid classes at lower levels.</P>
<P>I do hope the development team will balance our ability to tank mobs,they admit the nerf didn't work as planned.To c&#111;ncentrate &#111;n other aspects and give up &#111;n this is not a fix to the class it's a substitute appeasement and the m&#111;nk class as a whole is the &#111;nly loser in that.</P><!-- Signature --><br><br><span style="font-size:9px;">-----------------</span><br>Munkeesee Munkeedoo<br>
