              <td width="90%"  valign="top">
               <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1" bgcolor="#666666" width="100%">
                <tr> 
                 <td valign="top"> 
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="" height="147">
                   <tr> 
                    <td class="text" valign="top"><!-- Message body --><P>Here's the problem, Munkeesee.</P>
<P><BR>For the majority of 60-65 m&#111;nks in the game, if warriors do 100 damage, m&#111;nks do 120, and rogues do 190. Rangers can do from 90-150 depending &#111;n AAs, situati&#111;n, and gear. So m&#111;nks are WAY behind rogues, and just ahead of warriors, and sometimes ahead of, sometimes behind rangers.</P>
<P>Now, of those 4 classes, m&#111;nks are the absolute most fragile.</P>
<P>Looking at pure combat balance (which is all that really matters) rogues do the most damage by a very wide margin, and yet they greatly outtank m&#111;nks as well. So they are much better offensively, and somewhat better defensively. Rangers are also much better defensively than m&#111;nks, and they can also solo incredibly. (D&#111;n't kid yourself, a friend of mine in my guild, Locz Agneyastra, prides himself &#111;n soloing a good porti&#111;n of the way to 65 in PoV.) Warriors of course pull up the bottom &#111;n damage, slightly lower than m&#111;nks, but they tank incredibly well.<BR></P>
<P>M&#111;nks already had a severe handicap tanking because they simply didn't have enough hit points. The nerf was completely unnecessary. That being said, it's d&#111;ne, and if they aren't going to fix it, the class needs some rebalancing in other areas. Since it MUST be combat rebalancing, there is &#111;nly offense or defense to think about.&nbsp; A defensive increase would undo the nerf, so that leaves offensive.</P>
<P>There are &#111;nly a few ways to increase our offensive capabilities. Note I'm not advocating all of these, they are simply ideas.</P>
<P>1) Damage Table changes. I d&#111;n't like this &#111;ne, it's invisible to the naked eye and hard to determine exactly what it does.</P>
<P>2) Special attack changes. I really like this &#111;ne, although I d&#111;n't propose just turning FKick into a 360degree backstab. We aren't rogues. Although in the current balance state, we SHOULD outdamage rogues. I think the 2h weap&#111;n b&#111;nus should be applied to all special attacks that hit. I especially like this because it helps all m&#111;nks, regardless of equipment. I also think the caps &#111;n these skills should rise to 252, I miss far too much with FKick. </P>
<P>3) 1h Weap&#111;n B&#111;nus applied to sec&#111;ndary hand. Initially I love this idea, it would be unique to m&#111;nks and very easily adjustable. (for example, if this was too powerful, you could apply 50&#037; of the&nbsp;1h weap&#111;n b&#111;nus to the sec&#111;ndary hand). There is &#111;ne big problem with this however: It screws over m&#111;nks who've g&#111;ne 2h. To compensate, perhaps add a bit to the m&#111;nk 2h b&#111;nus as well. It'd work, but I d&#111;n't think I like it as much as toying with our special attacks.</P>
<P>4) Increased chances to crit, or give us crippling blows at all times (or crippling blow equivalents, like strikes to weak points/nervous system of our opp&#111;nent.) I sorta like the crippling blow idea.</P>
<P>5) This would result in refunding some people a lot of AAs, but the ultimate would simply be to have DW and DA fire 100&#037; of the time, quad attacks &#111;n every hit.&nbsp; Perhaps too powerful, but maybe not really, when you c&#111;nsider DW and DA &#037;ages are already approaching 80 with AAs.</P>
<P>Those are just a few ideas I have. Take 'em or leave 'em. Doesn't matter to me. I'm still having fun, it's just the principle of the thing. At my level I was never tanking anyway...</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
